Neither the regular msi or the reloaded setup file are working for me.

Please take this into consideration before downloading. I'm a veteran PC gamer and I have DV for PS3. This console to PC port is done without any regard to how it will play on your computer.

Controls:
The game controls are decent, but not great for a console game. They take a huge hit on PC however, as the calibration in a flight/action game like this should be decently suited for both mouse and key as well and a dual analog stick but I have both controls for PC and it doesn't feel even close to the PS3's control. Very awkward and clunky at best.

Graphics:
Honestly, it feels stripped down graphically. On the PS3 it looks more fluid and has a better field of depth. I'm running a top end system (Pi7 920 @ 3.2ghz, 6 gig 1600 ram, NV 285 GTX 2gig that runs anything out atm and with all settings maxed out, still looks lower quality than the console version. As mentioned, it runs in windowed mode with no option for full screen once you change your video settings. With a quick look at your profile in docs/games/capcom, it can be fixed.

Gameplay:
It's Dark Void! Isn't a "great" game on console, but it's a decent campaign overall.

Thoughts:
It was like they decided the PC version an after thought and stripped whatever wasn't compatible out. The game looks, plays and feels different on console and frankly, the 2 hrs I tried so hard to like what I did in the console version was wasted. Capcom did a great job porting Streetfighter 4. I'm an open minded gamer and know how to teak and adjust for optimum PC settings, but this game is one of the best examples of how NOT to port a game.

I know you'll d/l it and try it for yourself, but I thought you should know..

WINDOWED MODE problem fix:
You just need to edit the Defaultengine.ini file found in Capcom\Darkvoid\Nativepc\Skygame\config. Just open it up, Ctrl+F and search up "Fullscren" and change the 'FALSE' to TRUE and save.

Make sure to remove its Read-Only file attribute so that you can make this edit and save the .ini, and then you can set it back to read-only if you want.
